===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
From Middle English ''[[gyrle]]'' (child of either sex), of unknown origin; possibly from Old English ''*gyrele'' < Proto-Germanic ''*gurwilon-'' (diminutive of ''*gurwjoz'') < [[PIE]] ''*ghwrgh-''; another possibility is from Old English ''gierela'' ('garment').

